üß† NotionWealth Intelligence

An Agentic Decision Intelligence Platform for Financial & Capital Strategy

‚∏ª

Overview

NotionWealth Intelligence is an agentic decision platform that transforms fragmented financial disclosures into a continuously learning research, risk, and capital-intelligence system.

It is not a chatbot.

It is a multi-agent cognition layer designed to support:
	‚Ä¢	financial research
	‚Ä¢	risk and anomaly detection
	‚Ä¢	competitive intelligence
	‚Ä¢	portfolio-level reasoning
	‚Ä¢	capital allocation modeling
	‚Ä¢	traceable, replayable decision workflows

The core problem this system addresses is institutional cognition:

How do we build AI systems that do not just answer questions, but maintain memory, coordinate specialized agents, verify claims, replay past reasoning, and support real strategic and capital decisions?

‚∏ª

System Capabilities

üîπ Ingestion Agents
	‚Ä¢	Ingest 10-Ks, 10-Qs, earnings decks, transcripts, and market PDFs
	‚Ä¢	Parse, chunk, embed, and persist financial knowledge
	‚Ä¢	Extract both:
	‚Ä¢	semantic memory (vector store)
	‚Ä¢	structured financial facts

üîπ Multi-Layer Memory
	‚Ä¢	Semantic memory: qualitative, contextual, narrative knowledge
	‚Ä¢	Structured financial memory: metrics, segments, growth, risks
	‚Ä¢	Research memory: persisted research sessions and traces

üîπ Specialized Research Agents
	‚Ä¢	Financial agent: performance, growth, margins, segments
	‚Ä¢	Risk & anomaly agent: regulatory, operational, financial drift
	‚Ä¢	Competitive intelligence agent: cross-company positioning
	‚Ä¢	Portfolio agent: exposure, concentration, strategy themes

üîπ Control Plane
	‚Ä¢	Task routing and orchestration
	‚Ä¢	Verification and evidence attachment
	‚Ä¢	Research session generation
	‚Ä¢	Trace, audit, and replay support

üîπ Synthesis & Decision Agents
	‚Ä¢	Investment memo generation
	‚Ä¢	Capital allocation modeling
	‚Ä¢	Portfolio-level reasoning
	‚Ä¢	Strategic scenario construction

üîπ Research Replay Engine
	‚Ä¢	Persisted research sessions
	‚Ä¢	Replay and diff against new data
	‚Ä¢	Institutional learning and audit trail

üîπ Product Layer (UI)
	‚Ä¢	Run research workflows
	‚Ä¢	View verified outputs
	‚Ä¢	Replay past decisions
	‚Ä¢	Generate memos and portfolio briefs

